Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on designing a sequence of robot hand grasps for object recognition, and demonstrates results on a real robot. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses Monte Carlo tree search to approximate the optimal sequence of actions for object recognition. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although the paper focuses on tactile information, it still involves object recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a machine learning algorithm (Monte Carlo tree search) to optimize the sequence of actions for object recognition. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper involves designing a system (robot hand grasps) for object recognition.
